 wiesen die Krisen im Laufe des Jahrhunderts nicht nur alle zentralen Erscheinungsmerkmale moderner Spekulationskrisen auf, sondern nahmen sogar eine globale Reichweite mit erheblichen realwirtschaftlichen und sozialen Folgen an.  aSo far, scholarship has classified the speculation crises of the eighteenth century as having had no real economic consequences. This study aims to review this theory by looking at seven speculation crises. It concludes that these crises did not just have all of the central characteristics of modern speculation crises but also became global in scope with considerable economic and social consequences.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4a18. Jahrhundert. 4aKrise. 4aSpekulation. 4aWirtschaft. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aSpeculation.  acrisis.  aeconomy.  aeighteenth century.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831111197620 cprintz978311111456940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783111118383zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111118383zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111118383/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-GOA